== prompt 0 :: type=maven/com.example/java-example/example.Counter :: pass=type_summary ==
You are analyzing a Java class named Counter to summarize what it represents.

```
public class Counter {
    private int n;

    /** Creates a zeroed counter. */
    public Counter() {
        this.n = 0;
    }

    /** Increments by one, returns the new value. */
    public int bump() {
        this.n = Math.add(this.n, 1);
        return this.n;
    }

    /** Returns the current value. */
    public int value() {
        return this.n;
    }
}
```

Documentation: Counter accumulates a running total.

Methods:
- `public Counter()` — Creates a zeroed counter.
- `public int bump()` — Increments by one, returns the new value.
- `public int value()` — Returns the current value.

