- behavior: lifetime, mutability, thread-safety, cloneability, and any state transitions enforced by the methods
- invariants: conditions the type guarantees to hold between method calls (e.g. "value is always non-negative"); empty array if none apply
- security: sensitive data held, trust boundaries crossed, validation responsibilities; empty array if nothing security-relevant applies

